      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2256: SwarmLoaded is emitted before plugin body overwrites are loaded, so clients first receive unmodified message bodies and only later receive update signals. This contradicts the new ChatHandler contract that transformations happen before SwarmLoaded and can cause visible flicker/stale UI state. Load/apply overwrites before emitting SwarmLoaded, or transform the messages passed to the callback before emission.\n```suggestion\n#ifdef ENABLE_PLUGIN\nif (const auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock()) {\n    convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\n}\n#endif\nemitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n```",
