      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 127: updateMessageBodyOverwrite() accepts an arbitrary-size bodyOverwrite from plugin code and stores it in memory for the loaded conversation. A buggy or malicious plugin can repeatedly submit very large strings and force excessive daemon memory use. Enforce a reasonable size limit consistent with message body limits before storing/signalling the overwrite.\n```suggestion\nif (upd-\u003ebodyOverwrite.size() \u003e MAX_MESSAGE_BODY_SIZE) {\n    JAMI_WARNING(\"updateMessageBodyOverwrite: overwrite too large for {}/{}\", upd-\u003eaccountId, upd-\u003econversationId);\n    return -1;\n}\n```",
