      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 282: transformSwarmMessages() holds ChatServicesManager::mtx_ while calling plugin code. Other paths in this patch explicitly avoid invoking plugin callbacks under this mutex because handlers can call back into ChatServicesManager services; this path reintroduces the same deadlock risk during loadMissingBodyOverwrites()/message processing. Snapshot the enabled handlers under the lock, then invoke transformSwarmMessages() after releasing it.\n```suggestion\nstd::vector\u003cChatHandler*\u003e handlersToTransform;\n{\n    std::lock_guard const lk(mtx_);\n    // populate handlersToTransform from toggled/allowed handlers\n}\nfor (auto* handler : handlersToTransform) {\n    handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(messages, accountId, conversationId);\n}\n```",
